      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LITTLE SASSY BOY (2) looks close to a win after placing in both starts off a spell. Produced a very good effort last time at Wagga, coming from wider and finishing third and just 1.1 metres from the winner. Will enjoy a nice run from this favourable starting position and should be close to his peak now. TEESWIFT (1) is back from a spell of nine months and looks to be right up to the mark following a placing in a recent trial. His lone win came at this venue and he placed in both previous fresh attempts. Likely to get the favours from the inside draw so could make a winning return. MAJOR ISSUES (9) cops a tougher draw then when she won at this circuit and distance last start but she is progressing nicely. KAY JAY MIKI (7) is heading the right way, improving last time out to finish second from this row at Parkes.",
